.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-4-8::.
There are 6 different favourite beverages: hot-chocolate, iced-tea, milk, sprite, tea, water
The people use 6 different means of transport: bus, subway, snowmobile, skateboard, trike, train
 1. the person driving the subway is on the far left or far right##3
 2. the person driving the skateboard is on the left or right of the person drinking iced-tea##3
 3. the person driving the subway is on the right of the person driving the trike##1
 4. the person driving the snowmobile is on the left of the person driving the skateboard##1
 5. the person drinking iced-tea is on the left of the person drinking water##1
 6. the person driving the trike is on the right of the person drinking water##1
 7. the person driving the trike is in an odd position##4
 8. the person drinking milk is in an even position##4
 9. the person drinking milk is on the right of the person drinking hot-chocolate##1
10. the person driving the bus is in an odd position##4
11. the person drinking sprite is on the far right##1
12. the person driving the train is on the left of the person driving the trike##1

.:: Answer ::.
|            |       1       |    2     |    3     |       4       |     5      |      6       |
| Beverage   | hot-chocolate | milk     | iced-tea | water         | tea        | sprite       |
| Transport      | snowmobile       | skateboard | bus  | train | trike | subway |

